---
title: Chicken Thighs in Kimchi Sauce with an Asian Pear Slaw and Jasmine Rice
description: Kimchi (Korean pickles) typically come packed in a spicy brine that’s so good, you could just bottle it up and use it like your very own secret sauce. Well, guess what: we’ve done just that, using it to add some fiercely feisty personality to chicken thighs. Keeping with the Eastern theme, there’s also an Asian pear and sesame slaw on the side that counters the heat with bit of tang and sweetness, plus rice to soak up all that flavor.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chicken-thighs-in-kimchi-sauce-e2750c30.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-thighs-in-kimchi-sauce-4d05d4ac.pdf
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-thighs-in-kimchi-sauce-59ce4bb5c9fd0821325b9a52
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Korean
nutrition:
  calories: 640 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 680 mg
---

Bring ¾ cup water and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a #small pot{}.
Add @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup} and cover. Lower heat, reduce to a gentle simmer,
and cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Season @chicken thighs{12%oz} all over with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Add to pan and cook until browned and no longer pink in center,
about ~{5-6%minutes} per side. Remove pan from heat and let chicken cool
slightly.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve and core @Asian Pear{1}, then cut into
¼-inch-thick slices. Stack slices on top of each other and cut into thin
matchsticks. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@shallot{1} until you have about 2 TBSP.

Place @white wine vinegar{5%tsp} and @sugar{2%tsp} in a #small bowl{}. Add
sliced shallot (to taste— you may not use all). Stir to dissolve sugar.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside to pickle shallot.

Place @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, pear, cilantro, sliced shallot, shallot
pickling liquid, @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, and 1 TBSP oil in a #medium bowl{}.
Toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Add half the @kimchi hot sauce{4%oz} to pan with chicken. Toss to coat
chicken. Divide rice, slaw, and chicken between plates. Drizzle with remaining
kimchi sauce (to taste).

> Kimchi (Korean pickles) typically come packed in a spicy brine that's so good,
> you could just bottle it up and use it like your very own secret sauce. Well,
> guess what: we've done just that, using it to add some fiercely feisty
> personality to chicken thighs. Keeping with the Eastern theme, there's also
> an Asian pear and sesame slaw on the side that counters the heat with bit of
> tang and sweetness, plus rice to soak up all that flavor.